From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0026/N] metaspaceShared.cpp: declare oopmap buffer as bm_word_t*

Downstream fixup of patch 0007 (`BitMap::bm_word_t` changed from
`uintptr_t` to `uint64_t`). One call site declared its own buffer
as `uintptr_t* buffer` and passed it to `BitMap::write_to(bm_word_t*,
size_t)`. On a non-CHERI build `uintptr_t == unsigned long ==
uint64_t` so the type-check passed silently; on CHERI
`uintptr_t == unsigned __intcap` ≠ `bm_word_t`, and the compiler
correctly refuses the conversion.

Use `BitMap::bm_word_t*` for the buffer type so it tracks the
storage type regardless of platform.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0026)

--- a/src/hotspot/share/cds/metaspaceShared.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/cds/metaspaceShared.cpp
@@ -832,7 +832,7 @@ MetaspaceShared::dump_archive_heap_oopmaps(GrowableArray<MemRegion>* regions,
     ResourceBitMap oopmap = HeapShared::calculate_oopmap(regions->at(i));
     size_t size_in_bits = oopmap.size();
     size_t size_in_bytes = oopmap.size_in_bytes();
-    uintptr_t* buffer = (uintptr_t*)NEW_C_HEAP_ARRAY(char, size_in_bytes, mtInternal);
+    BitMap::bm_word_t* buffer = (BitMap::bm_word_t*)NEW_C_HEAP_ARRAY(char, size_in_bytes, mtInternal);
     oopmap.write_to(buffer, size_in_bytes);
     log_info(cds, heap)("Oopmap = " INTPTR_FORMAT " (" SIZE_FORMAT_W(6) " bytes) for heap region "
                         INTPTR_FORMAT " (" SIZE_FORMAT_W(8) " bytes)",
